            <div xml:id="TropicsNY"> 
                <interpGrp type="poembox">
                    <interp ana="#form" type="free"></interp>
                    <interp ana="#tone" type="sad"></interp>
                    <interp ana="#topic" type="society"></interp>
                </interpGrp>
                <lg> 
                    <l>Bananas ripe and green, and ginger-root,</l>
                        <l>Cocoa in pods and alligator pears,</l> 
                    <l>And tangerines and mangoes and grape fruit,</l>
                        <l>Fit for the highest prize at parish fairs,</l>
                    <l></l>
                    <l>Set in the window, bringing memories</l>
                        <l>Of fruit-trees laden by low-singing rills,</l>
                    <l>And dewy dawns, and mystical blue skies</l>
                        <l>In benediction over nun-like hills.</l>
                    <l></l>
                    <l>My eyes grew dim, and I could no more graze;</l>
                        <l>A wave of longing through my body swept,</l>
                    <l>And, hungry for the old, familiar ways,</l>
                        <l>I turned aside and bowed my head and wept.</l>
                    
